@notice Set the beneficiary address
 @param _beneficiary The beneficiary to receive sale proceeds
@notice Pause the coin machine if active
@notice Unpause the coin machine if paused
@notice Stop the coin machine (cannot be undone)

@notice Purchase tokens from Coin Machine.
 @param _numTokens The number of tokens to purchase
@notice Get the remaining balance of tokens
@notice Get the current price per token
@notice Get the number of remaining tokens for sale this period
@notice Get the minimum amount of tokens a user can purchase
@notice Get the maximum amount of tokens a user can purchase in a period
@notice Get the maximum amount of tokens a user can purchase in total

params._numTokens: The number of tokens to purchase

params._intakeCap: The maximum amount of purchaseToken we wish to receive
params._limits: The maximum and minimum amount of tokens a user can purchase (as percent of total sold)
params._periodLength: How long in seconds each period of the sale should last
params._startingPrice: The sale price to start at, expressed in units of _purchaseToken per token being sold, as a WAD
params._stoppable: Whether or not the sale can be paused or stopped prior to completion
params._targets: The target and maximum number of tokens to sell per period
params._times: The times to start and end the sale
params._tokens: The tokens we are selling and buying. Use 0x0 to buy Ether
params._windowSize: Characteristic number of periods that should be used for the moving average. In the long-term, 86% of the weighting will be in this window size. The higher the number, the slower the price will be to adjust

params._beneficiary: The beneficiary to receive sale proceeds

getCurrentPrice().notice: Get the current price per token

getMaxPurchase(address).notice: Get the maximum amount of tokens a user can purchase in a period

getMinPurchase().notice: Get the minimum amount of tokens a user can purchase

getSellableTokens().notice: Get the number of remaining tokens for sale this period

getTokenBalance().notice: Get the remaining balance of tokens

getUserLimit(address).notice: Get the maximum amount of tokens a user can purchase in total

initialise(address[2],uint256[2],uint256.notice: Must be called before any sales can be made

pause().notice: Pause the coin machine if active

stop().notice: Stop the coin machine (cannot be undone)

unpause().notice: Unpause the coin machine if paused
